ame%20seed%20and%20are%20native%20to%20eastern%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20eastern%20Russia%2C%20and%20Korea.%20The%20light%20brown%20ticks%20have%20been%20in%20the%20US%20since%20at%20least%202010%20and%20have%20spread%20to%20several%20eastern%20states%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aphis.usda.gov%2Fpublications%2Fanimal_health%2Ffs-longhorned-tick.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSDA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20invasive%20species%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20wildlife%20and%20has%20been%20found%20infesting%20animals%20like%20sheep%2C%20goats%2C%20dogs%2C%20cats%2C%20horses%2C%20deer%2C%20and%20people.%20They%20have%20even%20killed%20cattle.%20In%202021%2C%20a%20farmer%20in%20Ohio%20found%20three%20of%20his%20cows%20dead%20and%20covered%20in%20Asian%20longhorned%20ticks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ticks%20can%20also%20clone%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20or%20reproduce%20without%20a%20male%20%E2%80%94%20so%20a%20single%20tick%20is%20capable%20of%20starting%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aphis.usda.gov%2Fpublications%2Fanimal_health%2Falert-asian-longhorned-tick.508.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20laying%202%2C000%20eggs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEmerald%20ash%20borer%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20the%20shiny%20green%20emerald%20ash%20borer%20on%20a%20neutral%20green%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584bbf21c5c7b8c9a0b57e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPhoto%20of%20the%20invasive%20beetle%20emerald%20ash%20borer%20(Agrilus%20planipennis).%3Cp%3EMonique%20van%20Someren%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-guitars-are-changing-climate-crisis-ash-wood-fender-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemerald%20ash%20borer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20tiny%20beetle%20native%20to%20East%20Asia%20that%20was%20first%20detected%20in%20the%20US%20in%202002.%20About%20the%20size%20of%20a%20grain%20of%20rice%2C%20the%20beetle%20is%20a%20stunning%2C%20shiny%20shade%20of%20jewel%20green.%20Emerald%20ash%20borer%20infestations%20have%20been%20discovered%20in%2036%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20wood-boring%20pest%2C%20the%20invasive%20species%20lays%20its%20eggs%20on%20the%20bark%20of%20an%20ash%20tree.%20The%20larvae%20then%20carve%20their%20way%20into%20the%20tree%20and%20feed%20on%20its%20tissues.%20The%20boring%20disrupts%20the%20tree's%20food%20and%20water%20intake%2C%20eventually%20killing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20arriving%20in%20the%20US%2C%20emerald%20ash%20borers%20have%20decimated%20American%20ash%20trees%2C%20killing%20tens%20of%20millions%20across%20the%20country.%20Scientists%20say%20it's%20the%20most%20destructive%20pest%20ever%20to%20plague%20America's%20forests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFeral%20pigs%20and%20super%20pigs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Feral%20pigs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f7467f88f76900192cef2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20this%20Friday%2C%20Oct.%2025%2C%202019%20photo%2C%20feral%20pigs%20roam%20near%20LaBelle%2C%20Fla.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FRobert%20F.%20Bukaty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPigs%2C%20native%20to%20Europe%20and%20Asia%2C%20were%20brought%20to%20the%20US%20in%20the%201500s%20by%20early%20explorers%20as%20a%20source%20of%20food.%20Feral%20swine%20in%20the%20US%20today%20are%20the%20same%20species%20as%20pigs%20found%20on%20farms%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aphis.usda.gov%2Faphis%2Fourfocus%2Fwildlifedamage%2Foperational-activities%2Fferal-swine%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFeral%2520swine%2520were%2520first%2520brought%2Care%2520increasing%2520across%2520the%2520nation.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSDA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20are%20the%20descendants%20of%20pigs%20that%20either%20escaped%20or%20were%20released.%20Today%2C%20feral%20pigs%20can%20be%20found%20throughout%20the%20South%20and%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuper-pigs-bred-in-canada-escaped-captivity-now-invading-us-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsuper%20pigs%26quot%3B%20bred%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20also%20be%20invading%20the%20US%20from%20the%20north.%20The%20super%20pigs%2C%20a%20cross%20between%20a%20domestic%20pig%20and%20a%20European%20wild%20boar%2C%20were%20bred%20decades%20ago%20to%20make%20larger%20swine.%20The%20super%20pigs%20grow%20thick%2C%20furry%20coats%2C%20equipping%20them%20to%20survive%20winters%20in%20Canada%20and%20the%20northern%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pigs%2C%20which%20grow%20to%20well%20over%20600%20pounds%2C%20prey%20on%20native%20species%20like%20frogs%2C%20salamanders%2C%20and%20ground-nesting%20birds%20like%20ducks%20and%20geese.%20They%20also%20destroy%20agricultural%20crops%20by%20tearing%20up%20the%20land%20while%20rooting%20around%20for%20things%20like%20plant%20roots%20and%20insect%20larvae.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20some%20documented%20occurrences%20of%20the%20super%20pigs%20in%20North%20and%20South%20Dakota%2C%20but%20the%20animals%20have%20been%20unable%20to%20establish%20a%20permanent%20population%20%E2%80%94%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweird-invasive-species-damaging-us-environment-from-nutria-to-ticks-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703934181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584c1d6cefc010bea26873c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweird-invasive-species-damaging-us-environment-from-nutria-to