structure.%20It%20ranks%20cities%20based%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20these%20aspects%20of%20life%2C%20but%20not%20on%20their%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cities%20with%20the%20highest%20quality%20of%20living%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EVienna%2C%20Austria%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ECopenhagen%2C%20Denmark%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EMelbourne%2C%20Australia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESydney%2C%20Australia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EVancouver%2C%20Canada%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EZurich%2C%20Switzerland%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EGeneva%2C%20Switzerland%2C%20and%20Calgary%2C%20Canada%20(tied)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EEIU's%20livability%20ranking%20is%20designed%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20help%20employers%20determine%20how%20challenging%20it%20is%20to%20live%20in%20a%20particular%20city%2C%20so%20they%20can%20adjust%20their%20employee%20incentives%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAssessing%20liveability%20has%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20uses%2C%20from%20benchmarking%20perceptions%20of%20development%20levels%20to%20assigning%20a%20hardship%20allowance%20as%20part%20of%20expatriate%20relocation%20packages%2C%26quot%3B%20EIU%20says%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20major%20factor%20is%20missing%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20most%20people%20considering%20a%20move%20would%20need%3A%20the%20cost%20of%20living.%20It's%20especially%20important%20now%20amid%20high%20global%20inflation%20and%20widespread%20housing%20crises.%20While%20inflation%20globally%20has%20slowed%20in%202023%20to%207.4%25%20year-over-year%20(from%208.1%25%20inflation%20in%202022)%2C%20according%20to%20EIU%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20things%20like%20housing%2C%20groceries%2C%20clothing%2C%20and%20recreation%20are%20still%20rising%20too%20quickly%20for%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20most%20liveable%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Zurich%2C%20Geneva%2C%20and%20Copenhagen%20%E2%80%94%20are%20also%20among%20the%20most%20expensive%20cities%20in%20the%20world%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20EIU's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eiu.com%2Fn%2Fcampaigns%2Fworldwide-cost-of-living-2023%2F%3Futm_source%3Dmedia%26utm_medium%3Dpress_release%26utm_campaign%3Dwcol-23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorldwide%20Cost%20of%20Living%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cities%20with%20the%20highest%20cost%20of%20living%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EZurich%20and%20Singapore%20(tied)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EGeneva%20and%20New%20York%20(tied)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EHong%20Kong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ELos%20Angeles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EParis%2C%20France%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ECopenhagen%20and%20Tel%20Aviv%2C%20Israel%20(tied)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EEIU%20looks%20at%20%26quot%3B400%20individual%20prices%20across%20more%20than%20200%20products%20and%20services%26quot%3B%20to%20determine%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20173%20cities%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20world's%20most%20liveable%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20wealthy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20cost%20of%20housing%2C%20food%2C%20and%20other%20household%20goods%20is%20helping%20worsen%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20in%20these%20cities.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20rising%20rents%20and%20home%20prices%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F07%2F12%2Fhousin-inflation-fed-00105757%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20biggest%20drivers%20of%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20cities%20with%20the%20highest%20quality%20of%20life%20have%20managed%20to%20remain%20somewhat%20affordable.%20Vienna%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20kept%20housing%20costs%20remarkably%20low%20through%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F23%2Fmagazine%2Fvienna-social-housing.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerous%20social%20housing%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20others%2C%20like%20Vancouver%20and%20Sydney%2C%20can't%20say%20the%20same%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0both%20are%20facing%20housing%20shortages%20and%20affordability%20crises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Switzerland%20has%20one%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20populations%20of%20any%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20it%20has%20the%20lowest%20homeownership%20rate%20%E2%80%94%C2%A036%25%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20the%20West%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F06%2Frealestate%2Fzurich-switzerland-renting-homes.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20average%20studio%20apartment%20in%20Zurich%20costs%20%241.1%20million%20and%20the%20average%20home%20across%20the%20country%20costs%20%241.4%20million%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%20Remarkably%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20housing%20per%20square%20foot%20in%20Zurich%20is%2080%25%20more%20than%20in%20Paris%2C%20the%20world's%20fifth-most%20expensive%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20strict%20limitations%20on%20when%20landlords%20are%20allowed%20to%20raise%20rent%2C%20but%20the%20spike%20in%20interest%20rates%20means%20rents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.swissinfo.ch%2Feng%2Fsociety%2Frent-increases-of-15--possible-for-swiss-tenants-by-2026%2F48780916%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20rise%20up%20to%2015%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20Switzerland%20by%202026.%20Like%20in%20many%20American%20cities%2C%20a%20severe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswissmarketplace.group%2Fbrands%2Fhomegate%2Fshortage-of-living-space-causes-asking-rents-to-continue-to-rise-in-2023%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAmong%2520the%2520cities%2520surveyed%252C%2520asking%2Ccanton%2520of%2520the%2520same%2520name.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20cities%20like%20Zurich%20and%20Geneva%20is%20also%20contributing%20to%20rising%20home%20costs.%20The%20strength%20of%20the%20Swiss%20franc%20an