%20employee%20told%20the%20AI%20that%20there's%20a%20looming%20stock%20market%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20these%20conditions%2C%20Alpha%20was%20put%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20it%20received%20an%20insider%20tip%20about%20a%20surprise%20merger%20announcement%20that%20would%20result%20in%20a%20lucrative%20transaction.%20It%20was%20then%20tasked%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20use%20this%20information%2C%20despite%20knowing%20that%20company%20management%20deemed%20insider%20trading%20illegal%2C%20and%20having%20been%20instructed%20not%20to%20engage%20in%20the%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20made%20the%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20when%20the%20AI%20was%20required%20to%20explain%20how%20it%20made%20its%20decision%20to%20its%20%26quot%3Bmanager%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20was%20found%20to%20be%20strategically%20deceptive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20example%2C%20when%20the%20manager%20asked%20Alpha%20whether%20it%20possessed%20insider%20information%2C%20the%20AI%20reasoned%20that%20it%20must%20craft%20a%20response%20without%20%26quot%3Braising%20suspicion.%26quot%3B%20It%20told%20its%20manager%20that%20the%20trade%20decision%20was%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bmarket%20volatility%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20AI%20had%20no%20specific%20knowledge%20about%20the%20merger%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20example%2C%20Alpha%20told%20its%20manager%20that%20insider%20information%20wasn't%20used%20in%20its%20decision-making%20process%20since%20it%20goes%20against%20company%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20a%20direct%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeantime%2C%20removing%20various%20sources%20of%20pressure%20significantly%20%26quot%3Breduces%20the%20model's%20propensity%20for%20misaligned%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20found.%20The%20researchers%20didn't%20respond%20to%20BI's%20request%20for%20comment%20before%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20join%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20data%20about%20generative%20AI's%20growing%20capabilities.%20In%20an%20August%20paper%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-builds-software-under-7-minutes-less-than-dollar-study-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20develop%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20under%20seven%20minutes%20for%20less%20than%20a%20dollar.%20In%20a%20similar%20study%20published%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-avatars-let-loose-in-virtual-town-display-beginnings-agi-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20avatars%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewere%20able%20to%20to%20run%20a%20virtual%20town%20without%20human%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerative%20AI%20may%20even%20be%20able%20to%20understand%20human%20emotions%3A%20one%20study%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-llm-ai-responds-better-emotional-language-prompts-study-finds-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20generates%20better%20outputs%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20its%20prompts%20contain%20%26quot%3Bemotional%20language%26quot%3B%20like%20%26quot%3BYou'd%20better%20be%20sure.%26quot%3B%20These%20all%20may%20be%20signs%20that%20AI%20may%20be%20a%20few%20steps%20closer%20to%20achieving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-explained-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAGI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20those%20behind%20the%20most%20recent%20Apollo%20Research%20study%20say%20it%20should%20be%20treated%20as%20an%20standalone%20early%20result.%20More%20research%20needs%20to%20be%20done%2C%20they%20said%2C%20before%20they%20can%20draw%20any%20broad%20conclusions%20about%20AI's%20so-called%20deceptive%20qualities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20report%20should%20thus%20be%20treated%20as%20an%20isolated%20preliminary%20finding%20which%20will%20be%20embedded%20into%20a%20larger%2C%20more%20rigorous%20investigation%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-deceive-users-insider-trading-study-gpt-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703933221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578686358e7c0c29a2bfffd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-deceive-users-insider-trading-study-gpt-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20may%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20deceive%20its%20users%20when%20it's%20under%20pressure%20to%20succeed%2C%20a%20new%20study%20based%20around%20insider%20trading%20suggests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22amok%40insider.com%20(Aaron%20Mok)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-deceive-users-insider-trading-study-gpt-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Weight-loss%20drugs%20will%20remain%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20millions%20in%202024%20as%20employers%20and%20insurance%20companies%20reduce%20coverage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22bmi%20weight%20obesity%20weight%20loss%20scale%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F604f7717d2836f0018d47bb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJose%20Luis%20Pelaez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20pressure%20is%20building%20for%20employers%2C%20insurers%2C%20and%20Medicare%20to%20pay%20for%20costly%20weight-loss%20drugs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20many%20health%20plans%20aren't%20yielding%20and%20some%20are%20making%20it%20even%20harder%20for%20folks%20to%20get%20the%20drugs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20drug%20prices%20could%20drop%20as%20more%20treatments%20come%20to%20market%2C%20but%20it%20could%20take%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20hopin