20minutes.%20Alternatively%2C%20cook%20in%20an%20air%20fryer%20at%20200%C2%B0C%20for%2015%20to%2020%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Meanwhile%2C%20heat%20the%20butter%20in%20a%20large%20saucepan%20over%20a%20medium%20heat%20and%20fry%20the%20onion%20for%20five%20minutes%20until%20softened%2C%20then%20add%20the%20garlic%20and%20fry%20for%20a%20further%20two%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20In%20a%20bowl%20or%20jug%2C%20whisk%20together%20the%20milk%20and%20cream%20cheese%2C%20then%20add%20to%20the%20pan%20along%20with%20the%20chicken%20stock.%20Simmer%20aggressively%20for%2015%20minutes%2C%20stirring%20regularly%2C%20until%20reduced%20by%20half.%20If%20the%20milk%20starts%20to%20bubble%20over%2C%20reduce%20the%20heat%20so%20that%20it%20doesn't%20catch%20on%20the%20bottom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20Bring%20a%20large%20saucepan%20of%20salted%20water%20to%20the%20boil%20and%20cook%20the%20linguine%20until%20very%20al%20dente%20(around%20eight%20minutes)%2C%20then%20drain%2C%20reserving%20the%20pasta%20water.%20Rinse%20the%20pasta%20under%20cold%20water%20until%20completely%20cooled%2C%20then%20fill%20the%20pan%20with%20cold%20water%20and%20place%20the%20pasta%20back%20in%20the%20saucepan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20Once%20the%20sauce%20has%20reduced%20and%20is%20a%20nice%2C%20thick%2C%20creamy%20consistency%2C%20stir%20in%20the%20remaining%20Cajun%20seasoning%20and%20remove%20from%20the%20heat.%20Add%20the%20Parmesan%2C%20dried%20parsley%20and%20plenty%20of%20black%20pepper%2C%20then%20stir%20to%20combine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20Transfer%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20sauce%20to%20sauce%20pots%20for%20pouring%20over%2C%20then%20drain%20the%20pasta%20and%20add%20it%20to%20the%20pan%20along%20with%20a%20ladle%20of%20the%20pasta%20water.%20Toss%20to%20combine%20over%20a%20medium%20heat%2C%20adding%20more%20pasta%20water%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8.%20Divide%20the%20pasta%20into%20airtight%20containers.%20Slice%20the%20chicken%20and%20add%20to%20the%20pasta%2C%20then%20garnish%20with%20fresh%20parsley.%20This%20will%20keep%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%20up%20to%20four%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENutrition%20per%20serving%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E624%20calories%2C%2063.2%20grams%20carbs%2C%2050.9%20grams%20protein%2C%2020.4%20grams%20fat%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMiso%20ramen%20noodle%20jar%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Miso%20ramen%20noodle%20jars%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c38b87a3c8094d5dd62d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMiso%20ramen%20noodle%20jars%3Cp%3ELiz%20%26amp%3B%20Max%20Haarala%20Hamilton%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20noodle%20jars%20are%20one%20of%20those%20meal-prep%20hacks%20that%20will%20bring%20a%20smile%20to%20your%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirkland%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSimply%20pack%20your%20chicken%20or%20tofu%20into%20jars%20along%20with%20miso%20paste%2C%20noodles%20and%20vegetables%20and%20store%20in%20the%20fridge.%20Then%2C%20all%20you%20need%20to%20do%20is%20add%20boiling%20water%2C%20give%20it%20a%20stir%20and%20tip%20it%20all%20out%20into%20a%20bowl.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EServes%20four%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E200%20grams%20(7%20ounces)%20dried%20egg%20noodles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%20tablespoon%20sesame%20oil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E400%20grams%20(1%20%C2%BE%20cups)%20minced%20chicken%20or%201%20x%20450%20(2%20cups)%20gram%20block%20of%20firm%20tofu%2C%20crumbled%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20cloves%20of%20garlic%2C%20peeled%20and%20crushed%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E15%20grams%20(2%20tablespoons)%20fresh%20ginger%2C%20grated%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%20tablespoon%20soy%20sauce%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20tablespoons%20red%20miso%20paste%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E100%20grams%20(3.5%20ounces)%20m