2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anna%20Suvorova%2C%20Russian%20Scholar%20of%20Urdu%20and%20Islamic%20Cultural%20Mores%20of%20the%20Sub-Continent%2C%20Passes%20Away%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080050%2FUntitled-design-18-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnna%20Suvorova%2C%20a%20distinguished%20personality%20in%20the%20field%20of%20literature%20and%20art%20and%20a%20serious%20Russian%20scholar%20of%20Urdu%2C%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20age%20of%2075%20on%20November%2024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20no%20idea%20how%20many%20Urdu-speaking%20people%20know%20about%20her.%20In%20fact%2C%20when%20I%20shared%20the%20news%20of%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20passing%20with%20some%20of%20my%20friends%20in%20the%20literary%20circle%20it%20appeared%20from%20their%20response%20that%20they%20had%20heard%20the%20name%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20the%20newspapers%20had%20little%20information%20about%20her%20which%20is%20perhaps%20why%20there%20was%20no%20news%20of%20her%20passing%20anywhere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20reaction%20even%20from%20the%20people%20who%20were%20considered%20very%20close%20to%20Anna.%20However%2C%20she%20was%20remembered%20in%20some%20social%20media%20posts%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELeave%20aside%20common%20readers%2C%20prominent%20educational%20institutions%20in%20Lucknow%20and%20Delhi%2C%20where%20Anna%20had%20formed%20academic%20alliances%20in%20some%20way%20or%20the%20other%2C%20ought%20to%20have%20remembered%20her%2C%20but%20did%20not.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20only%20few%20people%20had%20heard%20or%20seen%20Anna%20gracefully%20speak%20Urdu%20in%20her%20Russian%20accent%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20she%20was%20an%20unfamiliar%20name%20in%20our%20academic%20sphere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBorn%20in%20Moscow%20on%20January%2011%2C%201949%2C%20Anna%20had%20engaged%20in%20academic%20activities%20at%20Lucknow%20University%20and%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20apart%20from%20the%20School%20of%20Oriental%20Studies%20(SOAS)%20and%20the%20National%20College%20of%20Arts%20(Lahore).%20She%20was%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Asian%20Literature%20Department%20at%20the%20Russian%20Academy%20of%20Sciences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENon-Russian%20readers%20like%20us%20know%20about%20the%20literary%20contribution%20of%20this%20scholar%20famous%20for%20doing%20fundamental%20and%20analytical%20research%20on%20Urdu%20literature%20in%20Russian%20language%20through%20English%20translations%20by%20translators%20like%20Osama%20Farooqui.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20was%20the%20second%20Russian%20Orientalist%2C%20after%20Ludmila%20Vassilyeva%20(although%20she%20was%20a%20contemporary%20Russian%20scholar%20and%20friend)%2C%20whose%20work%20was%20more%20familiar%20among%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent.%20Anna%20was%20not%20famous%20in%20India%20like%20Ludmila%20but%20in%20Pakistan%20she%20was%20quite%20a%20known%20figure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20had%20read%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20book%20Muslim%20Saints%20of%20South%20Asia.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20I%20came%20to%20know%20about%20her%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20What%20I%20liked%20about%20her%20research%20was%20that%20she%20had%20collated%20the%20biographies%20of%20Sufis%20and%20cited%20lots%20of%20references.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20book%20at%20hand%20currently%2C%20but%20in%20it%20she%20had%20even%20gathered%20and%20quoted%20Persian%20couplets%20which%20must%20have%20taken%20a%20lot%20of%20effort.%20The%20book%20left%20quite%20an%20impression%20on%20my%20mind.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20now%20that%20I%20am%20trying%20to%20look%20at%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20works%20sincerely%2C%20I%20remember%20a%20brief%20piece%20written%20by%20her%20titled%20%E2%80%9CIftikhar%20Arif%3A%20A%20Glimpse%20from%20a%20Distant%20Country%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20preface%20of%20the%20poetry%20collection%3Cem%3E%20The%20Twelfth%20Man%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Iftikhar%20Arif%2C%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20poets%20of%20our%20times%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20comes%20across%20as%20an%20astute%20reader%20and%20critic%20of%20poetry.%20She%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CA%20further%20aspect%20of%20Iftikhar%20Arif%E2%80%99s%20work%20may%20be%20termed%20%E2%80%98existential%E2%80%99.%20And%20this%20is%20the%20most%20universal.%20Always%20balancing%20on%20the%20knife-edge%20between%20life%20and%20death%2C%20hope%20and%20despair%2C%20love%20and%20emptiness%2C%20his%20poetry%20expresses%20the%20existential%20%E2%80%98homelessness%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20exile%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98loneliness%20of%20a%20human%20soul%20in%20a%20world%20loaded%20with%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20further%20adds%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThough%20deeply%20rooted%20in%20the%20classical%20tradition%20of%20Ghazal%20and%20the%20later%20Nazm%20poetry%2C%20Iftikhar%20Arif%E2%80%99s%20intellectual%20verse%20is%20too%20much%20of%20a%20child%20of%20our%20planet%20to%20belong%20to%20Urdu%20speaking%20readers%20only.%20The%20better%20the%20outer%20world%20comes%20to%20know%20his%20poetry%2C%20the%20more%20it%20will%20understand%20its%20miracle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20me%2C%20Iftikhar%20Arif%20is%20not%20a%20rebellious%20poet.%20Being%20a%20philosopher%20and%20a%20sharp%20observer%2C%20he%20is%20preaching%20a%20stoic%20dignity%20of%20endurance%20as%20a%20protest.%20Sometimes%20this%20way%20is%20longer%20and%20harder%20than%20revolt.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080418%2FWith-Mushtaq-Ahmad-Yusufi-Sahib-and-Iftikhar-Arif.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080418%2FWith-Mushtaq-Ahmad-Yusufi-Sahib-and-Iftikhar-Arif.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080418%2FWith-Mushtaq-Ahmad-Yusufi-Sahib-and-Iftikhar-Arif-300x222.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080418%2FWith-Mushtaq-Ahmad-Yusufi-Sahib-and-Iftikhar-Arif-1024x756.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691006%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22886%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAnna%20Suvorova%20w%3C%2Fspan%3Eith%20Mushtaq%20Ahmad%20Yusufi%20Sahib%20and%20Iftikhar%20Arif.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%2C%20literary%20experts%20will%20realise%20that%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20present%20such%20a%20balanced%20opinion%20without%20assessing%20and%20observing%20the%20poetic%20language%20and%20finesse%20of%20a%20poet.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Anna%2C%20it%20can%20be%20said%20with%20certainty%20that%20in%20one%20way%20or%20another%2C%20she%20was%20a%20diligent%20reader%20and%20critic%20of%20classic%20Urdu%20poetry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20connection%2C%20one%20might%20cite%20one%20of%20her%20prominent%20books%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMasnavi%3A%20A%20study%20of%20Urdu%20Romance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20though%20in%20almost%20every%20research%2Fcritical%20piece%2C%20she%20frequently%20appears%20to%20allude%20to%20Islamic%20culture%20and%20social%20as%20well%20as%20cultural%20studies%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20streams%20of%20Sufi%20and%20Bhakti%20traditions%20are%20also%20a%20natural%20part%20of%20her%20academic%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20book%2C%20she%20has%20extensively%20discussed%20the%20physical%20along%20with%20divine%20forms%20of%20love%20and%20romance%20with%20special%20reference%20to%20Urdu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emasnavi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20She%20also%20wrote%20in%20detail%20about%20the%20development%2C%20artistic%20behaviour%20and%20characteristics%20of%20this%20rare%20genre%20of%20Urdu%20poetry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnna%20has%20made%20every%20effort%20to%20make%20this%20book%20interesting%2C%20especially%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20Russian%20readers.%20However%2C%20as%20a%20reader%20of%20Urdu%20literature%2C%20I%20find%20her%20excessively%20leaning%20towards%20Sufism%20and%20Islamic%20philosophy%20in%20this%20book%20as%20well%20as%20other%20writings.%20It%20seems%20she%20believes%20that%20despite%20the%20constraints%20of%20her%20perspective%2C%20her%20message%20is%20incomplete%20without%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emasnavis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20northern%20India%20from%20seventeenth%20to%20nineteenth%20century%20quoted%20in%20this%20book%20are%20not%20merely%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20perusing%20the%20works%20of%20poets%20like%20Mir%20Taqi%20Mir%2C%20Mir%20Hasan%20Dehlvi%2C%20Ghulam%20Hamdani%20Mushafi%2C%20Dayashankar%20Naseem%20and%20Nawab%20Mirza%20Shauq%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20becoming%20well-acquainted%20with%20the%20historiography%20of%20the%20period.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20perhaps%20why%20the%20book%20offers%20a%20lot%20of%20vital%20information%20about%20lifestyle%2C%20customs%20and%20secular%20values%20as%20well%20as%20the%20historical%20and%20cultural%20environment%20of%20the%20period.%20She%20also%20discusses%20gender%20sensitivity%2C%20and%20with%20the%20help%20of%20commonplace%20examples%2C%20she%20highlights%20the%20patriarchal%20system%20prevalent%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20poetry%20of%20love%20mystery%20and%20divine%20love%20has%20been%20rarely%20seen%20and%20read%20in%20this%20style%2C%20although%20Urdu%20critics%20like%20Shakeelur%20Rahman%20had%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20such%20studies%20with%20their%20work%20on%20romance%20and%20its%20aesthetics.%20Anna%20herself%20was%20a%20great%20admirer%20of%20Rahman%2C%20and%20keeping%20in%20mind%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20she%20talked%20about%20his%20studies%2C%20it%20would%20be%20right%20to%20say%20that%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20style%20of%20criticism%20is%20on%20the%20same%20lines%20as%20the%20criticism%20of%20Rahman%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EElements%20of%20folk%20traditions%20or%20folk%20style%20are%20subtly%20placed%20in%20both%20their%20works.%20However%2C%20while%20the%20style%20of%20criticism%20is%20similar%2C%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20work%20seems%20more%20influenced%20by%20the%20Islamic%20tradition%20or%20philosophy%2C%20whereas%20in%20Shakilur%20Rahman%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20a%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20the%20Hindu%20pantheon%20is%20visible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EComparing%20the%20two%20is%20not%20the%20aim%20here.%20But%20while%20reading%20Anna%2C%20Shakilur%20Rahman%20inevitably%20comes%20to%20mind.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080607%2FWith-Intizar-Hussain.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080607%2FWith-Intizar-Hussain.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080607%2FWith-Intizar-Hussain-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080607%2FWith-Intizar-Hussain-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691007%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAnna%20Suvorova%20with%20Intizar%20Hussain.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnna%E2%80%99s%20field%20of%20study%20includes%20Indo-Islamic%20culture%20which%20contains%20Sufi%20and%20Bhakti%20traditions.%20In%20addition%2C%20she%20has%20a%20strong%20interest%20in%20Urdu%20theatre%2C%20Urdu%20drama%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edastan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Urdu%20language%20and%20literature.%20She%20even%20attempted%20to%20write%20the%20history%20of%20Urdu%20theatre%20and%20Urdu%20drama%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20texts%20of%20plays.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20she%20connects%20the%20concept%20of%20Urdu%20drama%20with%20Islamic%20beliefs%2C%20and%20in%20this%20matter%20her%20ideology%20appears%20dogmatic.%20She%20seems%20to%20be%20propagating%20her%20views%20more%20like%20an%20expert%20on%20religion%20and%20its%20philosophy%20than%20a%20literary%20scholar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%20one%20might%20view%20her%20ideology%2C%20there%20was%20some%20influence%20of%20Indo-Islamic%20culture%20on%20her%20personality%20as%20well.%20Perhaps%20that%20is%20why%20some%20people%20had%20recently%20specifically%20noted%20that%20Anna%20even%20preferred%20to%20wear%20shalwar-kameez%20as%20her%20attire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%20to%20literary%20works%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20books%20on%20Lahore%2C%20Benazir%20Bhutto%20and%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Jinnah.%20Many%20people%2C%20who%20read%20her%20book%20on%20Lahore%2C%20called%20it%20an%20important%20text%20on%20cultural%20history%20and%20a%20major%20reason%20behind%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20in%20Pakistan.%20Another%20prominent%20work%20of%20Anna%20is%20Widows%20and%20Daughters%2C%20a%20book%20focusing%20on%20six%20Asian%20women%20including%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20Benazir%20Bhutto%20and%20Sheikh%20Hasina%2C%20their%20rise%20to%20power%20and%20their%20status%20as%20women%20leaders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20writing%20these%20books%2C%20Anna%20was%20perhaps%20also%20studying%20the%20political%20history%20of%20Asia%2C%20which%20is%20perhaps%20why%20she%20describes%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Jinnah%20as%20her%20most%20admired%20personality.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20who%20was%20also%20awarded%20with%20Sitara-e-Imtiaz%20by%20Pakistan%2C%20is%20related%20to%20the%20country.%20It%20includes%20her%20contribution%20to%20Pakistani%20literature%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHer%20book%20on%20the%20erstwhile%20culture%20of%20Lucknow%20is%20also%20a%20significant%20text.%20According%20to%20Russian%20scholar%20Ludmila%20Vassilyeva%2C%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20book%20on%20the%20history%20of%20Urdu%20culture%20is%20important%20not%20only%20from%20the%20academic%20point%20of%20view%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%20interesting%20for%20the%20common%20readers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELudmila%20also%20calls%20her%20an%20expert%20in%20visual%20arts%20and%20painting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20claimed%20that%20Anna%20had%20translated%20the%20stories%20of%20many%20writers%20like%20Manto%20from%20Urdu%20to%20Russian.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20scholar%20of%20Modern%20Urdu%20Literature%20Alexey%20S.%20Sukhochov%20(1928-2000)%2C%20who%20is%20known%20for%20his%20book%20Dastan%20Se%20Novel%20Tak%2C%20was%20the%20teacher%20of%20both%20Ludmila%20Vassilyeva%20and%20Anna%20Suvorova%20and%20their%20PhD%20supervisor%20as%20well.%20Alexey%E2%80%99s%20book%20on%20Makhdoom%20Muhiuddin%20is%20quite%20popular.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETalking%20about%20Anna%20and%20Ludmila%E2%80%99s%20initial%20education%20in%20Urdu%2C%20a%20teacher%20at%20Moscow%20University%20Professor%20Olgazhmovotova%20introduced%20them%20to%20books%20of%20basic%20Urdu%20language.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20today%20after%20Anna%E2%80%99s%20departure%2C%20to%20look%20at%20her%20work%20is%20to%20see%20the%20cultural%20history%20of%20two%20countries%2C%20to%20understand%20their%20political%20and%20social%20concerns%2C%20to%20go%20through%20the%20secular%20values%20of%20Sufi%20and%20Bhakti%20traditions%20and%20to%20witness%20the%20glorious%20past%20of%20Urdu%20literature%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20linguistic%20exchange%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703903874000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30080050%2FUntitled-design-18-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fanna-suvorova-russian-scholar-of-urdu-passes-away%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Her%20work%20encompasses%20a%20vast%20range%2C%20from%20Sufi%20and%20Bhakti%20poetry%20to%20biographies%20of%20Jinnah%20and%20books%20on%20Lahore%20and%20Lucknow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fanna-suvorova-russian-scholar-of-urdu-passes-away%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parliament%2C%20CAG%2C%20EC%3A%20More%20Pillars%20Crumble%20as%20Modi%20Tightens%20Hold%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F28144222%2FIMG_0206.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20really%20a%20bad%20time%20for%20the%20Indian%20democracy.%20The%20year%202023%20witnessed%20the%20Modi%20establishment%20extending%20its%20control%20on%20democratic%20institutions%20like%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fwho-is-girish-chandra-murmu-cag-and-trusted-aide-of-pm-modi-since-gujarat-days%2Farticle66913528.ece%5C%22%3ECAG%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Indian%20parliament%20looks%20more%20like%20Turkish%20president%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdo%C4%9Fan%E2%80%99s%20Grand%20National%20Assembly.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20begin%20with%20the%20subjugation%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20organisation.%20The%20electoral%20victory%20in%20Hindi%20hinterland%20has%20put%20Modi%20in%20a%20triumphalist%20mood.%20The%20process%20of%20centralisation%20and%20bureaucratisation%20of%20the%20organisation%20is%20now%20complete.%20Chief%20ministers%20are%20fixed%20at%20will%20by%20Amit%20Shah%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20internal%20experts.%20This%20time%2C%20even%20the%20formalities%20like%20the%20parliamentary%20board%E2%80%99s%20endorsement%20and%20central%20observers%E2%80%99s%20report%20have%20been%20done%20away%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20the%20central%20observers%20carried%20a%20sealed%20cover%20which%20contained%20the%20name%20of%20the%20high%20commands%20choice%20for%20the%20chief%20ministership.%20And%20the%20observers%20respectfully%20opened%20it%20and%20declared%20the%20winner.%20The%20sealed%20cover%20is%20a%20symbol%20of%20authority%20which%20every%20one%20in%20the%20party%20must%20accept%20without%20grudge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGone%20are%20the%20days%20when%20those%20those%20enjoying%20maximum%20support%20among%20the%20elected%20MLAs%20should%20take%20the%20cake.%20The%20GenX%20BJP%20CMs%20are%20not%20answerable%20to%20MLAs%20or%20their%20electors%20but%20high%20command.%20No%20one%20else.%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20trust%20is%20most%20crucial.%20Otherwise%20you%20lose%20the%20job%20within%20weeks.%20That%20is%20the%20story%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fdata-tirath-singh-rawat-vacates-office-in-less-than-four-months-cms-with-shortest-stints%2Farticle61443832.ece%5C%22%3ETirat%20Singh%20Rawat%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20four-month%20tenure%20as%20Uttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20CM%3C%2Fa%3E%20tells%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sealed%20cover%20doctrine%20is%20a%20Gujarat%20model.%20It%20was%20first%20introduced%20when%20Bhupendra%20Patel%20replaced%20Vijay%20Rupani%20as%20chief%20minister%20in%202021.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20CEO-style%20imposition%20had%20become%20the%20norm.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20choice%20of%20the%20new%20CMs%20%E2%80%93%20Bhajan%20Lal%20Sharma%2C%20Mohan%20Yadav%20and%20Vishudeo%20Sai%20%E2%80%93%20follows%20a%20pattern%3A%20confirmed%20RSS%20background%20with%20tilak%20on%20forehead%2C%20less%20known%20outside%20the%20state%20if%20not%20first%20timers%20and%20with%20little%20following%20in%20the%20state.%20They%20perpetually%20look%20to%20high%20command%20for%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20very%20first%20action%20of%20the%20new%20CMs%20was%20to%20issue%20full-page%20advertisements%20in%20Delhi%20with%20their%20photos%20with%20PM.%20They%20all%20look%20to%20Adityanath%20and%20Manohar%20Lal%20Khattar%20as%20role%20models.%20So%20much%20so%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fbhopal-news%2Fmadhya-pradesh-cm-mohan-yadav-bans-meat-sales-in-open-101702525512937.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMadhya%2520Pradesh%2527s%2520newly%2520appointed%2520chief%2Cfirst%2520cabinet%2520meeting%2520on%2520Wednesday.%26amp%3Btext%3D%25E2%2580%259CAfter%2520the%2520implementation%2520of%2520food%2Cand%2520fish%2520in%2520the%2520open%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20decision%20of%20new%20MP%20cabinet%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20to%20ban%20sale%20of%20meat%20and%20eggs%20in%20public%20places%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBulldozers%20roam%20on%20the%20streets%20looking%20for%20the%20right%20targets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20parliament%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20parliament%20is%20the%20latest%20to%20fall%20for%20the%20new%20imperious%20style.%20During%20the%20winter%20session%2C%20a%20record%20number%20of%20146%20opposition%20MPs%20%E2%80%93%20100%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%2046%20from%20Rajya%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20suspended.%20During%20the%20Modi%20rule%2C%20expulsions%20and%20suspensions%20in%20parliament%20shot%20up%20by%2071%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%202019%2C%20presiding%20officers%20resorted%20to%20suspensions%20at%20the%20drop%20of%20a%20hat.%20During%20this%20winter%20session%2C%20every%20day%20the%20Speaker%20and%20Chairman%20drew%20up%20a%20list%20of%20what%20they%20called%20violators%20of%20discipline%20and%20went%20on%20announcing%20the%20names%20of%20MPs%20to%20be%20suspended.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20least%20in%20one%20case%2C%20name%20of%20a%20MP%20who%20was%20on%20leave%20was%20included.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20suspension%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fsr-parthiban-dmk-mp-suspended-for-lok-sabha-protest-on-sick-leave-9068452%2F%5C%22%3Ewithdrawn%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20the%20error%20was%20pointed%20out%20by%20the%20concerned%20member.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20all%20began%20with%20the%20jumping%20of%20two%20youths%20into%20the%20House%20from%20the%20visitors%20gallery%20%E2%80%93%20again%20a%20first%20%E2%80%93%20to%20highlight%20the%20growing%20unemployment.%20To%20heighten%20the%20drama%2C%20the%20youths%20burst%20smoke%20canisters.%20They%20had%20pamphlets%20calling%20PM%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepaper.telegraphindia.com%2Fimageview%2F455447%2F53040909%2Fundefined.html%5C%22%3Emissing%20person%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3