ndia.com%2Fimageview%2F455457%2F5533014%2Fundefined.html%5C%22%3Eto%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepaper.telegraphindia.com%2Fimageview%2F455457%2F5533014%2Fundefined.html%5C%22%3Ethe%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepaper.telegraphindia.com%2Fimageview%2F455457%2F5533014%2Fundefined.html%5C%22%3EHouse%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20gave%20an%20account%20of%20the%20line%20of%20investigations%20into%20attack.%20The%20government%20side%20also%20allowed%20a%20short%20duration%20discussion%20in%20both%20Houses.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20parliament%20remained%20paralysed%20for%20weeks%20together%20when%20BJP%20was%20in%20the%20opposition%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20coal%20allocations.%20Such%20expressions%20of%20dissent%20were%20always%20viewed%20as%20legitimate%20mode%20of%20expressing%20democratic%20protest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20senior%20ministers%20of%20the%20Modi%20cabinet%20%E2%80%93%20Sushma%20Swaraj%20and%20Arun%20Jaitely%20%E2%80%93%20had%20in%20the%20past%20forcefully%20disagreed%20with%20what%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20Dhankhar%20now%20describe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fparliament-gridlock-democracy-bjp-8057195%2F%5C%22%3Eviolation%20of%20parliamentary%20discipline%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20September%207%2C%202012%2C%20Swaraj%20had%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CNot%20allowing%20Parliament%20to%20function%20is%20a%20form%20of%20democratic%20protest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJaitely%2C%20senior%20minister%20and%20close%20aide%20of%20Modi%20even%20when%20L.K.%20Advani%20was%20in%20contest%20for%20the%20prime%20ministership%2C%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20Parliament%20is%20used%20to%20ignore%20issues%E2%80%A6%20parliamentary%20obstruction%20is%20not%20undemocratic.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20Jaitely%20said%20so%20at%20Ranchi%20on%20January%2030%2C%202011.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20late%20colleagues%20of%20prime%20minister%20Modi%20were%20simply%20reiterating%20the%20existing%20the%20parliamentary%20traditions.%20Disruptions%20have%20never%20considered%20as%20a%20punishable%20offence%20deserving%20suspensions.%20It%20is%20a%20pernicious%20practice%20now%20being%20imposed%20by%20the%20two%20incumbent%20presiding%20officers.%20Apparently%2C%20parliamentary%20management%20has%20become%20part%20of%20the%20larger%20Modi%20project%20to%20perpetuate%20a%20system%20of%20duopoly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20political%20thinker%20Pratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%20describes%20as%20%E2%80%98India%E2%80%99s%20monumental%20tragedy.%E2%80%99%20Parliament%20as%20an%20institution%20of%20functioning%20democracy%20is%20effectively%20dead%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fpratap-bhanu-mehta-parliamentary-democracy-bharat-india-mps-suspension-9077660%2F%5C%22%3Ehe%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20hit%20the%20bull%E2%80%99s%20eye%20when%20he%20says%20that%20Modi%20wields%20power%20without%20any%20seriously%20effective%20constitutional%20limitations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20happened%20in%20the%20House%20since%20the%20mass%20suspensions%20confirm%20this%20conclusion.%20With%20the%20opposition%20benches%20nearly%20empty%2C%20ministers%20came%20and%20bulldozed%20bills.%20Amit%20Shah%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Famp%2Findia%2Fstory%2Frajya-sabha-passes-new-criminal-law-amendment-bills-opposition-mps-2479009-2023-12-21%5C%22%3Epushed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20three%20bills%20affecting%20the%20entire%20criminal%20justice%20system%20by%20voice%20vote%20in%20both%20Houses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDemand%20from%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20women%20for%20more%20time%20to%20discuss%20the%20bills%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesnownews.com%2Findia%2Fwomen-bjp-m