ubious%20circumstances%20and%20six%20Nepalis%20have%20been%20reportedly%20killed%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20investigate%20the%20number%20of%20Nepalis%20fighting%20for%20Ukraine.%20Some%20have%20also%20joined%20the%20French%20Foreign%20Legion%2C%20such%20is%20the%20adverse%20effect%20of%20Nepal%20apparently%20rejecting%20Agniveer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20Army%20Chief%20General%20Mukund%20Naravane%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EFour%20Stars%20of%20Destiny%3C%2Fem%3E%20spills%20the%20beans%20over%20the%20ownership%20of%20Agniveer%20scheme.%20As%20we%20have%20known%2C%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Frss-ajit-doval-coerced-agniveer-scheme-on-the-army-rahul-gandhi-in-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F97693965.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ethrust%20on%20the%20three%20services%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20(PMO)%20and%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20(NSA)%20Ajit%20Doval%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20stated%20in%20parliament.%20Originally%20designed%20by%20late%20General%20Bipin%20Rawat%2C%20it%20was%20to%20be%20a%20pilot%20project%20for%205%2C000%20Army%20personnel%20but%20the%20transformative%20reform%20took%20all%20three%20services%20by%20surprise%20says%20Naravane.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20month%20at%20the%20Army%E2%80%99s%20Chanakya%20Dialogue%20a%20former%20Navy%20chief%20said%20that%20former%20CNS%20Admiral%20Karamvir%20Singh%20had%20rejected%2C%20in%20writing%2C%20the%20draft%20Agniveer%20scheme.%20Despite%20this%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20manipulation%20of%20incumbent%20service%20chiefs%20in%20praising%20the%20Agniveer%20project%20is%20astounding.%20What%20no%20government%20or%20military%20official%20has%20revealed%20is%20the%20stalemate%20over%20recruitment%20of%20Nepali%20Gorkha%20Agniveers%20since%20June%202022%20and%20the%20Covid%20embargo%20period.%20Had%20General%20Rawat%2C%20a%20second%20generation%20Gorkha%20officer%20been%20alive%2C%20Agniveer%20in%20its%20current%20avatar%20would%20not%20have%20materialised.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20spent%20the%20last%20month%20in%20Pokhara%2C%20Nepal%2C%20the%20heartland%20of%20Nepal%20Domiciled%20Gorkhas%20(NDG)%20recruitment%2C%20interacting%20with%20ex-servicemen%20and%20other%20stakeholders.%20Not%20a%20single%20NDG%20has%20been%20recruited%20or%20become%20an%20Agniveer%20for%20nearly%20four%20years.%20Nepal%C2%A0%20has%C2%A0%20not%20communicated%20any%20reason%20for%20not%20subscribing%20to%20the%20Agniveer%20project.%20The%20Tripartite%20Treaty%20of%201947%20governed%20Gorkha%20recruitment%20from%20Nepal%20by%20the%20British%20and%20Indian%20Armies.%20In%20June%202022%2C%20India%20announced%20the%20Agnipath%20scheme%20without%20consulting%20Nepal.%20Gorkhas%20are%20recognised%20as%20great%20warriors%20around%20the%20world%20and%20were%20key%20to%20the%20British%20empire%20that%20extended%20from%20Honduras%20to%20Hong%20Kong.%20In%202014%2C%20prime%20minister%20Modi%20praised%20the%20Gorkhas%20for%20shedding%20their%20blood%20for%20protecting%20the%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20India.%20For%20India%2C%20Gorkhas%20joining%20Indian%20Army%20is%20much%20more%20that%20%E2%80%98recruitment%E2%80%99.%20It%20represents%20the%20strategic%20bonding%20between%20India%20and%20Nepal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-china-army-nepali-gorkhas-worry%5C%22%3EWhy%20India%20Should%20Be%20Worried%20About%20Chinese%20Army%E2%80%99s%20Plans%20to%20Recruit%20Nepali%20Gorkhas%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20Congress%20led%20government%20in%202022%20passed%20on%20the%20decision%20on%20Agniveer%20to%20the%20new%20Maoist-led%20government%20which%20said%20it%20was%20seeking%20political%20consensus%20%E2%80%93%20diplomatic%20euphemism%20for%20rejecting%20Agniveer.%C2%A0%20In%20Nepal%2C%20public%20view%20on%20the%20scheme%20is%20divided.%C2%A0%20Most%20find%20it%20to%20be%20deeply%20flawed%20but%20their%20bottom%20line%20is%20firmly%20centered%20on%20pensionary%20benefits.%20The%20generous%20One%20Rank%2C%20One%20Pension%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(OROP)%20has%20transformed%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20of%20the%20ex-servicemen.%20The%20minority%20view%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20(Agniveer)%20is%20better%20than%20nothing%E2%80%9D%20highlights%20the%20need%20of%20job-seekers%20even%20if%20it%20for%20four%20years%20sans%20pension.%20But%20politics%20has%20trumped%20strategic%20and%20financial%20factors.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20elections%2C%20Communist%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20CPN%20UML%2C%20CPN%20Maoist%20and%20CPN%20Socialist%20%E2%80%93%20captured%2068%25%20of%20the%20vote.%20The%20Maoists%E2%80%99%2040-point%20demand%20in%201990%20prior%20to%20the%20civil%20war%20demanded%20abrogation%20of%20foreign%20recruitment%20especially%20in%20Indian%20Army.%20No%20government%20in%20the%20coalition%20era%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20that%20has%20become%20inevitable%20under%20the%20new%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20can%20oppose%20Communist%20thinking%2C%20especially%20on%20Agniveer.%20The%20hope%20that%20under%20the%20power-sharing%20agreement%2C%20after%20one%20year%2C%20the%20Nepali%20Congress-led%20coalition%20will%20accept%20Agniveer%20is%20unrealistic.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20Nepal%20Army%20Chief%20Lt.%20General%20Prabhu%20Sharma%2C%20who%20is%20also%20an%20honorary%20General%20in%20the%20Indian%20Army%20said%20that%20he%20is%20not%20against%20recruitment%20in%20Indian%20Army%20but%20he%20is%20against%20recruitment%20as%20Agniveer.%20In%201974%2C%20an%20unstrategic%20Indian%20project%20to%20terminate%20Gorkha%20recruitment%20was%20aborted%3B%C2%A0%20then%20Army%20chief%2C%20General%20Gopal%20Bewoor%20from%2011%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20persuaded%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20dump%20the%20lunatic%20scheme.%20Today%20we%20have%20a%20Chief%20of%20Defence%20Staff%2C%C2%A0%20General%20Anil%20Chauhan%2C%20from%20same%20the%20Gorkha%20regiment%20but%20the%20manner%20of%20his%20deep%20selection%20has%20compromised%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%2C%20for%20now%2C%20is%20determined%20not%20to%20budge%20from%20Agniveer%20.%20Two%20reasons%20are%20offered%20%E2%80%93%20first%2C%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20end%20Gorkha%20recruitment%20as%20there%20is%20sufficient%20male%20recruitable%20population%20(MRP)%20in%20India.%20The%20more%20compelling%20reason%20is%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%20of%20dismantling%20colonial%20legacy%20of%20recruitment%20of%20foreign%20soldiers.%20The%20real%20reason%20though%20is%20financial%20%E2%80%93%20salary%20and%20pension%20costs.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAgniveer%20is%20designed%20to%20reduce%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20Army%20and%20cut%20pensions.%20The%20latter%20alone%20in%202021-22%20accounted%20for%20Rs%201.21%20lakh%20crore%20which%20was%20more%20than%20allotment%20for%20modernisation.%20Av%20(Agniveer)%20is%20the%20rank%20prefix%20of%20a%20soldier%20and%20is%20the%20lowest%20rank%20in%20PBOR%20(Personnel%20Below%20Officer%20Rank).%20This%20is%20a%20new%20rank%20and%20tenable%20by%20Agniveers.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENepal%20is%20conveying%20to%20India%20that%20Agniveer%20is%20breach%20of%20Tripartite%20Agreement%20of%201947%20and%20consensus%20is%20required%20between%20original%20signatories%20to%20change%20terms%20of%20engagement%3B%20and%20in%20order%20to%20accept%20Agniveer%2C%20the%20ruling%20government%20is%20seeking%20political%20consensus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20future%20of%20the%20Gorkha%20Brigade%20and%20its%2038%20battalions%20is%20bleak%20given%20the%20inflexible%20positions%20of%20both%20countries.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20year%2C%20after%20returning%20from%20Nepal%2C%20following%20his%20appointment%20as%20honorary%20General%20of%20Nepal%20Army%2C%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%2C%20General%20Manoj%20Pandey%20said%20this%20on%20Gorkha%20recruitment%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20decide%20soon%20their%20vacancies%20will%20be%20given%20to%20others%E2%80%9D.%20As%20there%20has%20been%20no%20recruitment%20for%20four%20years%2C%20a%20shortfall%20in%20Gorkha%20regiment%20is%20being%20made%20up%20by%20Kumaonis%2C%20Garhwalis%20and%20now%20Nagas%20while%20other%20tribes%20are%20being%20considered.%20General%20Pande%20is%20also%20mulling%20over%20reducing%20Gorkha%20battalions.%20Indian%20Domiciled%20Gorkhas%20who%20constitute%2040%25%20of%20recruitment%20are%20not%20a%20match%20for%20NDGs.%20In%202017%2C%206%2F1%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20was%20raised%20comprising%20100%25%20IDGs.%20It%20has%20become%20difficult%20now%20to%20preserve%206%2F1%20GR%E2%80%99s%20IDG%20sanctity%20and%20content%20as%20few%20IDGs%20meet%20the%20qualitative%20requirements%20(QRs)%20even%20after%20lowering%20standards%20and%20fewer%20are%20available.%20So%20the%20plan%20to%20fill%20up%20NDG%20shortfall%20with%20IDGs%20is%20a%20non-starter.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20his%20visit%20to%20India%20in%20June%2C%20prime%20minister%20Dahal%20did%20not%20raise%20the%20issue%20of%20Agniveer.%20Nepali%20foreign%20minister%20Narayan%20Saud%20told%20the%20BBC%20in%20August%20that%20any%20alteration%20of%20Tripartite%20Treaty%20between%20Nepal%2C%20India%20and%20UK%20must%20be%20based%20on%20consensus.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EStrangely%2C%20neither%20Nepal%20nor%20India%20has%20cared%20to%20call%20for%20talks%20on%20Agniveer.%20Meanwhile%2C%20recruitment%20is%20restricted%20to%20IDGs%20and%20tradesmen.%20The%20Gorkha%20Training%20Centres%20are%20training%20them%20and%20Agniveers%20of%20Indian%20regiments.%C2%A0%20The%20Colonel%20of%20Gorkha%20Brigade%20Lt.%20General%20Ajai%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20also%20General%20Officer%20Commanding%20(GOC)%20in%20C%20Southern%20Command%20and%20has%20served%20in%20Nepal%2025%20years%20ago%20as%20a%20Pension%20Paying%20Officer%2C%20is%20visiting%20Nepal%20as%20President%20of%20the%20Gorkha%20Brigade%20next%20month%20and%20will%20meet%20cabinet%20ministers%20and%20government%20officials%20besides%20ex-servicemen%20.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20stunning%20irony%20that%20just%20when%20India%20is%20celebrating%20the%20biopic%20Sam%20Bahadur%20on%20Field%20Marshal%20Manekshaw%2C%20who%20became%20a%20household%20name%20in%20India%20and%20Nepal%20owing%20to%20his%20bonding%20with%20Gorkhas%2C%20their%20downsizing%20and%20ultimate%20phasing%20out%20is%20becoming%20a%20reality.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202030%20there%20will%20be%20no%20pure%20Gorkha%20battalions%20and%20about%20half%20present%20number%3B%20and%20by%202037%2C%20none%20at%20all.%20This%20government%20will%20be%20credited%20with%20ending%20foreign%20recruitment%20but%20snapping%20a%20strategic%20connection%20with%20the%20most%20crucially%20located%20neighbour%20while%C2%A0%20opening%20the%20door%20to%20Nepali%20Gorkhas%20in%20PLA%20in%20the%20not%20too%20distant%20future.%20India-Nepal%20relations%20will%20never%20be%20the%20same%20again.%20Not%20a%20happy%20new%20year%20for%20the%20Gorkha%20Brigade!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshok%20K.%20Mehta%2C%20a%20major%20general%2C%20is%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Defence%20Planning%20Staff%20now%20the%20Integrated%20Defence%20Staff.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703777426000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F25161451%2F27440629405_563f1699dc_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Funhappy-new-year-for-the-gorkha-brigade-downsizing-and-ultimate-phasing-out-becoming-a-reality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20government%20will%20be%20credited%20with%20ending%20foreign%20recruitment%20but%20also%20of%20snapping%20a%20strategic%20connection%20with%20a%20crucially%20located%20neighbour%20while%C2%A0opening%20the%20door%20to%20Nepali%20Gorkhas%20in%20PLA%20in%20the%20not%20too%20distant%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A102%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Funhappy-new-year-for-the-gorkha-brigade-downsizing-and-ultimate-phasing-out-becoming-a-reality%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Extraordinary'%3A%20Man%20rescued%20six%20days%20after%20crashing%20car%20-%20surviving%20only%20on%20rainwater%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703777160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-indiana-police-crash_6406158.jpg%3F20231228155252%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Findiana-man-rescued-six-days-after-crashing-car-surviving-only-on-rainwater-13038717%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20man%20was%20trapped%20inside%20his%20crashed%20pickup%20truck%20for%20six%20days%2C%20drinking%20rainwater%20to%20survive%2C%20before%20fisherman%20finally%20spotted%20and%20rescued%20him%2C%20Indiana%20police%20have%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A156%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Findiana-man-rescued-six-days-after-crashing-car-surviving-only-on-rainwater-13038717%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Findiana-man-rescued-six-days-after-crashing-car-surviving-only-on-rainwater-13038717%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Findiana-man-rescued-six-days-after-crashing-car-surviving-only-on-rainwater-13038717%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BJP%20Leaders%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Karnataka%20Allege%20Graft%20Within%20Party%3B%20National%20Secy.%20Sacked%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28200750%2FHazra-N-Nadda.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20A%20BJP%20national%20secretary%20from%20West%20Bengal%2C%20who%20accused%20leaders%20of%20the%20state%20unit%20for%20allegedly%20diverting%20funds%20from%20a%20Gita%20Path%20event%2C%20was%20removed%20from%20his%20central%20post%20earlier%20this%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20on%20December%2024%2C%20Anupam%20Hazra%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20on%20his%20social%20media%20account%20that%20passes%20for%20the%20Gita%20Path%20program%20at%20the%20Brigade%20Parade%20Grounds%20were%20being%20sold%20by%20party%20leaders%20at%20Rs%201%2C000%20per%20head.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20VIP%20passes%20were%20made%20for%20Gita%20Path%20for%20some%20VIP%20people.%20It%20was%20given%20to%20block-level%20leaders%20of%20BJP%20to%20be%20given%20to%20some%20people.%20However%2C%20in%20Birbhum%E2%80%99s%20Nalhati%2C%20these%20cards%20are%20being%20sold%20for%20Rs%201%2C000%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fbjp-anupam-hazra-bengal-jp-nadda-9085017%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20quoted%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20demanded%20an%20enquiry%20into%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20days%20later%2C%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20BJP%20president%20J.P.%20Nadda%20were%20in%20Kolkata%20to%20review%20preparations%20for%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20next%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Tuesday%20night%2C%20it%20was%20announced%20that%20Hazra%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20his%20post%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20central%20unit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20the%20instructions%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20National%20President%20J.P.%20Nadda%2C%20Anupam%20Hazra%20is%20relieved%20from%20the%20post%20of%20national%20secretary.%20This%20should%20be%20followed%20with%20immediate%20effect%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20BJP%20national%20general%20secretary%20Arun%20Singh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20Poush%20Mela%20in%20Santiniketan%2C%20Hazra%20set%20up%20a%20booth%2C%20encouraging%20discontented%20BJP%20members%20and%20dissatisfied%20workers%20to%20express%20their%20grievances%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHazra%20has%20had%20run-ins%20with%20the%20party%20leadership%20both%20at%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20professor%20at%20Visva-Bharati%20University%2C%20he%20had%20first%20been%20elected%20in%202014%20from%20the%20Bolpur%20constituency%20on%20a%20TMC%20ticket%2C%20having%20defeated%20the%20CPI(M)%20by%20over%202.5%20lakh%20votes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20had%20then%20alleged%20being%20disallowed%20from%20taking%20independent%20decisions%20due%20to%20the%20political%20influence%20of%20powerful%20party%20leaders%20from%20his%20region%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20being%20expelled%20from%20the%20party%20in%20January%202019%2C%20he%20joined%20the%20BJP%20and%20got%20a%20ticket%20for%20the%20Jadavpur%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%2C%20but%20lost%20to%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Mimi%20Chakraborty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202020%2C%20Hazra%20was%20appointed%20as%20national%20secretary%20by%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20central%20leadership%2C%20taking%20over%20from%20Rahul%20Sinha%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20state%20unit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20BJP%20leadership%20reappointed%20Hazra%20as%20national%20secretary%20for%20a%20second%20consecutive%20term.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20developments%20in%20West%20Bengal%20come%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20turmoil%20in%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Karnataka%20unit%2C%20which%20is%20also%20facing%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20from%20within%2C%20reflecting%20apparent%20infighting%20between%20two%20factions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fkarnataka%2Fbjp-mla-says-yediyurappa-was-involved-in-rs-40000cr-corruption-in-covid-management%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Basangouda%20Patil%20Yatnal%2C%20a%20BJP%20MLA%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20accused%20former%20BJP%20chief%20minister%20B.S.%20Yediyurappa%20of%20acquiring%20face%20masks%20at%20an%20inflated%20rate%2C%20resulting%20in%20irregularities%20totaling%20Rs%2040%2C000%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20News%20Minute%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYatnal%20also%20asserted%20that%20the%20Congress%20government%20was%20involved%20in%20trying%20to%20conceal%20the%20alleged%20scam.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKarnataka%E2%80%99s%20Congress%20chief%20minister%20Siddaramaiah%20urged%20Yatnal%20to%20submit%20all%20pertinent%20documents%20to%20the%20Justice%20Nagamohan%20Das%20Commission%2C%20which%20was%20investigating%20allegations%20related%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9840%25%20commission%E2%80%99%20allegations%20made%20by%20contractors%20during%20the%20previous%20BJP%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKarnataka%20BJP%20general%20secretary%20P.%20Rajeev%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20the%20party%20had%20taken%20note%20of%20certain%20recent%20developments%20and%20would%20not%20tolerate%20any%20activities%20that%20cause%20damage%20to%20its%20dignity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndoor%20discussions%20cannot%20be%20disclosed.%20What%20I%20can%20say%20is%20that%20the%20party%20will%20not%20tolerate%20any%20activities%20that%20cause%20damage%20to%20its%20dignity.%20Serious%20discussions%20have%20happened%20within%20four%20walls%2C%20and%20our%20central%20leadership%20will%20take%20an%20appropriate%20decision%20at%20an%20appropriate%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwont-tolerate-damage-to-party-dignity-bjp-on-leaders-corruption-charge-4752529%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERajeev%20told%20reporters%20in%20Bengaluru%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703775053000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28200750%2FHazra-N-Nadda.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-national-secy-anupam-hazra-removed-from-role%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Karnataka%20MP%20from%20the%20BJP%20alleged%20earlier%20this%20week%20that%20the%20B.S.%20Yediyurappa%20government%20acquired%20face%20masks%20at%20an%20inflated%20rate.%20The%20party's%20state%20leadership%20said%20it%20had%20taken%20note%20of%20recent%20developments%20and%20would%20not%20tolerate%20activities%20that%20damage%20the%20party's%20dignity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-national-secy-anupam-hazra-removed-from-role%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Memoir%20Chronicles%20How%20Israel%20Failed%20to%20Become%20the%20Promised%20Land%20for%20All%20Jews%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F15164743%2Ftaylor-brandon-Y8r0RTNrIWM-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CQu%E2%80%99est-ce%20qu%20%E2%80%98une%20nation%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhat%20is%20a%20nation%3F)%2C%E2%80%9D%20French%20scholar%20Ernest%20Renan%20had%20famously%20asked%20in%201882.%20A%20nation%20was%20not%2C%20he%20suggested%2C%20a%20racial%2C%20linguistic%2C%20religious%20or%20geographical%20construct%3B%20instead%2C%20it%20was%20%E2%80%98a%20spiritual%20principle%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20was%20forged%20through%20%E2%80%9Cforgetting%20%E2%80%A6%5Bor%5D%20historical%20error.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20a%20nation%20is%20one%20that%20has%20agreed%20to%20forget%20certain%20things%20in%20its%20past.%20Avi%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20memoir%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20Worlds%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20turns%20the%20spotlight%20back%20on%20some%20of%20the%20things%20that%20the%20Jewish%20nation%2C%20centred%20on%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20prefers%20to%20forget%20or%20suppress.%20It%20is%20a%20moving%20history%20of%20not%20just%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20pre-eminent%20historians%20and%20observers%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20also%20of%20a%20lost%20world%20in%20which%20Arabs%20and%20Jews%20had%20a%20shared%20past%20and%20a%20shared%20presence%2C%20one%20in%20which%20there%20was%20nothing%20preordained%20in%20the%20hostility%20that%20defines%20their%20current%20existence.%20In%20the%20words%20of%20the%20author%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%201947%20%E2%80%93%2049%2C%20it%20was%20not%20only%20the%20land%20of%20Palestine%20that%20was%20partitioned%2C%20but%20also%20the%20past.%20The%20common%20past%20of%20Jews%20and%20Muslims%20in%20Iraq%20was%20superseded%20by%20the%20new%20reality%20of%20the%20Arab-Israeli%20conflict.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20361px)%2085vw%2C%20361px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent-665x1024.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22361%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent-665x1024.jpeg%20665w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent-195x300.jpeg%20195w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent.jpeg%20779w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690940%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22556%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThree%20Worlds%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew.%20Oneworld%20Publications%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnsurprisingly%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20political%20book.%20Reading%20it%20today%20as%20the%20fires%20of%20conflict%20rage%20yet%20again%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20the%20enormity%20of%20what%20was%20lost%20in%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20was%20born%20and%20shaped%20by%20its%20first%20leaders%20is%20thrown%20into%20stark%20relief%20by%20the%20rising%20body%20count%20in%20the%20region.%20Then%20again%2C%20this%20is%20a%20memoir%20of%20loss.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Shlaim%20calls%20it%20a%20%E2%80%98revisionist%20tract%2C%20a%20transgressive%20document.%E2%80%99%20The%20transgression%20lies%20in%20identifying%20proudly%20as%20an%20Arab-Jew%20whose%20family%20had%20been%20integrated%20into%20the%20life%20and%20culture%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%3B%20caught%20in%20the%20cross-fire%20of%20Zionism%20and%20Arab%20nationalism%2C%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20family%20were%20compelled%20to%20move%20to%20the%20fledgling%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20move%20that%20is%20lamented%2C%20not%20lauded.%20The%20very%20hyphen%20in%20his%20identity%2C%20which%20celebrates%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20roots%20in%20Iraq%2C%20is%20anathema%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20lonely%20outpost%20of%20Jewish%20sanctuary%20in%20a%20sea%20of%20Arab%20hostility.%20The%20revisionism%20comes%20from%20questioning%20the%20founding%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20uniformly%20good%20thing%20for%20all%20Jews%2C%20because%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98monumental%20injustice%E2%80%99%20done%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20late%201940s%2C%20the%20founding%20of%20Israel%20produced%20another%20set%20of%20victims%3A%20the%20Jews%20of%20Arab%20lands%2C%20such%20as%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20who%20were%20alienated%20by%20the%20Zionist%20project%20from%20the%20land%20of%20their%20birth%2C%20from%20their%20culture%2C%20their%20languages%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20from%20their%20history.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShlaim%20was%20born%20into%20upper%20middle-class%20Iraqi-Jewish%20family%20in%201945%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20son%20of%20a%20prosperous%20businessman%2C%20whose%20family%2C%20and%20whose%20wife%E2%80%99s%20family%20traced%20their%20roots%20back%20to%20Iraq%20for%20generations.%20(Shlaimi%E2%80%99s%20maternal%20great-grandfather%20moved%20to%20India%20to%20make%20his%20fortune%2C%20working%20for%20the%20Sassoons%20in%20Bombay%2C%20before%20eventually%20moving%20back%20to%20Baghdad.)%20They%20were%2C%20quite%20simply%2C%20%E2%80%98Iraqis%20whose%20religion%20happened%20to%20be%20Jewish.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Shlaims%20were%20fully%20integrated%20into%20Iraqi%20society%2C%20speaking%20Arabic%2C%20mixing%20with%20Muslims%20and%20Jews%2C%20and%20thinking%20of%20themselves%20as%20native%20to%20that%20multicultural%20land%20%E2%80%93%20an%20Iraq%20where%20%E2%80%98the%20main%20criterion%20for%20differentiating%20between%20Jews%20and%20Arabs%20%E2%80%A6%20was%20religion%2C%20and%20only%20as%20an%20identifying%20characteristic%20and%20not%20a%20divisive%20one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20changed%20with%20the%20founding%20of%20Israel.%20Israel%20gave%20Judaism%20a%20territorial%20base.%20While%20this%20was%20a%20sanctuary%20for%20European%20Jews%20still%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20for%20the%20Jews%20of%20the%20Near%20East%2C%20the%20founding%20of%20a%20homeland%20for%20all%20Jews%20undermined%20their%20roots%20in%20Babylon%20that%20could%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20sixth%20century%20BCE.%20Jews%20had%20been%20a%20protected%2C%20yet%20well-integrated%20minority%20under%20the%20Ottoman%20Empire.%20At%20the%20start%20of%20the%20first%20world%20war%2C%20Jews%20constituted%20one%20third%20of%20Baghdad%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20a%20city%20that%20was%20often%20regarded%20as%20Jewish.%20Within%20years%20of%20the%20end%20of%20the%20second%20world%20war%2C%20Baghdad%E2%80%99s%20Jewish%20population%20was%20all%20but%20gone.%20They%20were%20victims%20of%20a%20political%20struggle%20between%20two%20competing%20%E2%80%98secular%E2%80%99%20ideologies%20of%20Arab%20nationalism%20and%20Zionism%20%E2%80%93%20one%2C%20that%20made%20them%20feel%20less%20welcome%20in%20the%20land%20of%20their%20birth%2C%20and%20the%20other%20that%20insisted%20that%20they%20could%20only%20be%20safe%20in%20the%20land%20of%20their%20religion.%20And%20thus%20the%20Shlaim%20family%20lost%20the%20land%20of%20their%20birth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20chronicle%20of%20loss%20begins%20with%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20Israel%20at%20the%20age%20of%20five.%20A%20combination%20of%20general%20attacks%20on%20Jews%20(some%20of%20which%20the%20historian%20in%20him%20has%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20Zionist%20underground%20%E2%80%93%20an%20attempt%20to%20push%20Jews%20towards%20the%20newly%20created%20Israel)%20and%20a%20specific%20sense%20of%20insecurity%20caused%20by%20criminals%20targeting%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20wealth%2C%20had%20caused%20his%20mother%20to%20conclude%20that%20Iraq%20was%20unsafe%20for%20the%20family.%20The%20move%2C%20however%2C%20extracted%20a%20heavy%20toll.%20They%20left%20behind%20their%20comfortable%20home%20and%20lifestyle%2C%20their%20language%2C%20their%20culture%2C%20their%20history%2C%20their%20past%2C%20and%20even%20their%20names.%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20mother%20and%20older%20sister%20yielded%20to%20the%20pressure%20to%20adopt%20more%20Hebrew%20names%3B%20Avi%E2%80%99s%20name%20morphed%20from%20Abi%20(for%20Abraham)%20to%20Avi%20(Avraham).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20375px)%2085vw%2C%20375px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194705%2FAvi_Shlaim.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194705%2FAvi_Shlaim.jpg%20375w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194705%2FAvi_Shlaim-225x300.jpg%20225w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690942%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAvi%20Shlaim.%20Photo%3A%20Mans2014%2FWikimedia%20commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20some%20of%20the%20most%20moving%20parts%20of%20this%20story%2C%20Shlaim%20explores%20what%20the%20move%20meant%20for%20his%20father%2C%20Yusef%20Shlaim%2C%20who%20arrived%20in%20Israel%20after%20his%20wife%20and%20children%2C%20having%20stayed%20behind%20to%20try%20to%20settle%20his%20affairs.%20Yusef%20was%20broken%20by%20the%20relocation.%20Until%20the%20age%20of%2050%2C%20he%20had%20been%20a%20successful%20Iraqi%20Jew%2C%20steeped%20in%20the%20ways%20and%20customs%20of%20the%20land%20of%20his%20birth.%20The%20move%20to%20Israel%20stripped%20him%20of%20it%20all.%20His%20standing%20in%20society%2C%20his%20wealth%2C%20his%20self-worth%2C%20all%20of%20it%20disappeared%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Zion%20where%20Arabic%20culture%20was%20actively%20suppressed.%20At%20its%20most%20basic%2C%20the%20move%20stripped%20him%20of%20his%20language%2C%20for%20Yusef%20was%20never%20able%20to%20communicate%20fluently%20in%20Hebrew.%20Arabic%20was%20looked%20down%20upon%2C%20and%20in%20one%20searing%20episode%2C%20Avi%20describes%20how%2C%20as%20a%20little%20boy%2C%20he%20squirmed%20in%20embarrassment%20when%20his%20father%20came%20across%20him%20playing%20with%20his%20friends%20and%20spoke%20to%20him%20in%20Arabic.%20The%20language%20of%20his%20forefathers%20had%20become%20a%20source%20of%20shame%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98promised%20land%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYusef%E2%80%99s%20story%20encapsulates%20the%20plight%20of%20so%20many%20Iraqis%20forced%20to%20leave%20their%20homes%2C%20only%20to%20find%20themselves%20treated%20like%20second%20class%20citizens%20in%20the%20promised%20land.%20They%20became%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eolim%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20immigrants%2C%20pushed%20down%20the%20pecking%20order%20that%20favoured%20the%20Ashkenazi%20or%20European%20Jews.%20Those%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20North%20Africa%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Sephardi%20Jews%20%E2%80%93%20were%20considered%20culturally%20and%20socially%20inferior%20and%20were%20expected%20to%20integrate%20into%20a%20conception%20of%20Israel%20as%20an%20outpost%20of%20European%20enlightenment%20in%20a%20sea%20of%20primitive%20Arabic%20culture.%20The%20point%20is%20not%20just%20the%20material%20loss%20%E2%80%93%20though%20of%20course%20that%20was%20considerable.%20The%20more%20painful%20loss%20was%20that%20of%20history%2C%20of%20language%2C%20of%20self.%20In%20order%20for%20Israel%20to%20be%20a%20Jewish%20haven%20in%20hostile%20Arab%20neighbourhood%2C%20the%20links%20between%20Jews%20and%20Arabs%20had%20to%20be%20completely%20disavowed.%20The%20move%20to%20Israel%20erased%20a%20whole%20culture%20and%20history%20of%20being.%20Yusef%20was%20not%20able%20to%20reinvent%20himself%20and%20he%20died%20a%20silent%20shadow%20of%20his%20prosperous%2C%20generous%20self.%20Avi%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20a%20lament%20for%20people%20like%20his%20father%20who%20lost%20literally%20everything%20in%20the%20move%20to%20Zion%2C%20for%20whom%20Zion%20became%20the%20land%20of%20exile.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20this%20point%20of%20view%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMemoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20reckoning%20with%20a%20heritage%20and%20a%20past.%20In%20addition%20to%20acknowledging%20the%20injustice%20done%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enaqba%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20catastrophe%20of%201948%2C%20when%20over%20750%2C000%20Palestinians%20were%20forcibly%20displaced%20from%20the%20land%20of%20their%20ancestors%20(events%20that%20occur%20outside%20the%20purview%20of%20this%20memoir)%2C%20this%20book%20looks%20at%20the%20injustice%20done%20to%20Arab-Jews%20who%20were%20pushed%20out%20of%20the%20lands%20of%20their%20birth%20by%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20region.%20As%20with%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20who%20were%20denied%20the%20right%20of%20return%20by%20the%20new%20Jewish%20state%2C%20the%20injustice%20done%20to%20the%20Arab-Jews%20was%20then%20compounded%20by%20the%20devaluing%20and%20suppressing%20of%20their%20identities%20in%20Israel.%20They%20were%20brought%20in%20to%20Israel%20to%20fill%20the%20%E2%80%98empty%20spaces%E2%80%99%20created%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20Palestine%E2%80%99%2C%20even%20if%20they%20%E2%80%98had%20no%20desire%20whatsoever%20to%20relocate%20to%20Israel.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Then%2C%20to%20maintain%20the%20idea%20of%20Israel%20as%20an%20outpost%20of%20Jewish%20sanctuary%2C%20the%20links%20of%20the%20Arab-Jews%20to%20the%20land%20of%20their%20forefathers%20had%20to%20be%20denied%20and%20suppressed.%20The%20Jews%20of%20the%20Arab%20lands%20could%20have%20been%20a%20bridge%20to%20their%20Arab%20neighbours%20once%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20was%20established%20in%20Palestine.%20Instead%2C%20David%20Ben-Gurion%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%2C%20%E2%80%98built%20Israel%20as%20a%20fortress%20state%20with%20a%20siege%20mentality%20that%20attributed%20genocidal%20intentions%20to%20its%20neighbours.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20price%20for%20that%20decision%20is%20still%20being%20paid%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20third%20home%20in%20this%20memoir%20of%20%E2%80%98Three%20Worlds%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20that%20is%20London%2C%20which%20is%20where%20Avi%20Shlaim%20moved%20from%20Israel%20to%20complete%20his%20secondary%20education.%20He%20never%20moved%20back.%20Britain%20provided%20the%20foil%20for%20Israel%20in%20a%20way%2C%20because%20the%20social%20distinctions%20between%20Ashkenazi%20and%20Sephardi%20did%20not%20matter%20so%20much.%20He%20was%20now%20freer%20to%20shape%20his%20identity%20as%20he%20chose.%20Eventually%2C%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20distance%20allowed%20Avi%20to%20bring%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20objectivity%20to%20his%20study%20of%20Israel.%20This%20gradually%20resulted%20in%20his%20disillusionment%20with%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20as%20it%20is%20now%20and%20the%20Zionist%20project%20that%20deprived%20him%20of%20his%20homeland.%20As%20he%20explains%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20present%20impasse%20in%20Israel-Palestine%20resulted%2C%20at%20least%20partly%2C%20from%20the%20central%20assumption%20of%20Zionist%20discourse%2C%20namely%2C%20that%20Jews%20and%20Arabs%20are%20exclusive%20and%20antagonistic%20ethnic%20categories.%20The%20Zionist%20movement%20was%20in%20origin%20and%20in%20essence%20a%20European%20movement%20led%20by%20European%20Jews%20who%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20Jewish%20state%20for%20European%20Jews.%20It%20aspired%20to%20be%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20but%20not%20of%20the%20Middle%20East.%20It%20sought%20not%20the%20melding%20of%20cultures%20but%20the%20replacement%20of%20the%20local%20culture%20by%20a%20European%20one.%20By%20its%20very%20nature%2C%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20deepened%20the%20divisions%20between%20Israelis%20and%20Palestinians%2C%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20between%20Judaism%20and%20Islam%2C%20between%20Hebrew%20and%20Arabic.%20The%20Zionist%20movement%20and%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%20have%20actively%20worked%20to%20erase%20our%20common%20past%2C%20our%20intertwined%20histories%20and%20our%20centuries-old%20heritage%20of%20pluralism%2C%20religious%20tolerance%2C%20cosmopolitanism%20and%20co-existence.%20Above%20all%2C%20Zionism%20has%20discouraged%20us%20from%20seeing%20each%20other%20as%20fellow%20human%20beings.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20that%2C%20in%20essence%20is%20why%20this%20book%20is%20a%20must-read.%20Avi%20reminds%20us%20that%20beneath%20even%20the%20most%20intractable%20of%20conflicts%20are%20human%20beings%20%E2%80%93%20people%20with%20histories%2C%20cultures%20and%20stories.%20Once%20we%20allow%20ourselves%20to%20understand%20those%20histories%20and%20acknowledge%20the%20essential%20humanity%20of%20each%20other%2C%20we%20might%20start%20to%20find%20a%20way%20out%20of%20even%20the%20most%20impossibly%20antagonistic%20of%20relationships.%20It%20is%2C%20quite%20simply%2C%20an%20excellent%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPriyanjali%20Malik%20walked%20into%20her%20first%20tutorial%20with%20Avi%20Shlaim%20some%20twenty-five%20years%20ago.%20He%20guided%20her%20through%20her%20MPhil%2C%20provided%20advice%20on%20life%20and%20relationships%20and%20taught%20her%20how%20to%20become%20a%20scholar%20somewhere%20along%20the%20way.%20He%20even%20approved%20of%20the%20chap%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20marry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22tooltip%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703773177000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F15164743%2Ftaylor-brandon-Y8r0RTNrIWM-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-memoir-chronicles-how-israel-failed